onally, I rather have a secure position than hope for an opening, even if it means me waiting an extended amount of time.<br>Also there will be people that do not feel this list fits them, and will try and kill rage.  Nothing can be done with this, there will not be a perfect system.  Atleast this may be a means to set some sort of agreement on this horrid camp.<br>As far as the list holder, I believe it should be the responsiblity of the top 3 clerics to watch out for each other and take names down of all clerics that want to participate.  I believe there is a good mix of clerics from various dragon enabled killing guilds.  Its great people giving pros and cons, but why dont we try and lessen the stress this gives to our clerics.<br>My advice to the clerics that want this, is to just do it.  If people give you slack or just choose to kill it let them.  As long as you keep order and make an effort, I am sure people in time will learn to respect it.<br>   <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/uzarax1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zarax1</A> at: 5/23/02 7:29:31 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/ulluweyen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lluweyen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>1st post by this guy</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/23/02 7:57:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3100.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Cleric Ragefire List</span><hr size=1> WTG Softly! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/utukk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tukk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>S & M</span><br>  Posts: 38<br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/23/02 7:58:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub